Despite downturns in commercial investments, Ultimus Holdings, a Pan-African investment company, has expanded its Nigeria luxury fitting portfolio, with the launching of The Classroom in Lagos.
 
The firm also planned to invest a total of $400m in the next 10 years.
  
President and Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Ultimus Holdings, Dr. Ifeanyi Odii, disclosed this at the unveiling of The Classroom, a luxury fittings showroom.
   
Odii noted that The Classroom, is primed to spread its footprints to 10 African countries in 10 years and that it is a first-of-its-kind ambiance fitting showroom located in Victoria Island, Lagos.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .